text: Alba Caride (April 24, 1980, Vigo, Province of Pontevedra) is a Spanish rhythmic gymnast. Caride competed for Spain in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she tied for 11th place in the qualification and advanced to the semifinal, in the semifinal she was 19th and didn't advance to the final of 10 competitors. == References == == External links == * * Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Spanish rhythmic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Spain Category:Sportspeople from Vigo
